static AdvTupleCursor AdvTupleCursor.automagicallyCreateTupleCursor(java.lang.Iterable<?> it, java.lang.String alias)
          This factory creates an AdvTupleCursor for Iterables (Lists, ...) containing arbitrary types and does an "automagical" mapping: If the elements are Objects of a primitive type (or pseudo-Primitive like Integer, String, ...) the Tuples in the resulting Cursor will just contain one element called "value".
